        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n\n- Avoid the voice-call plugin's duplicate OpenAI realtime greeting by making proactive/manual OpenAI speech an instructed `response.create` instead of injecting a synthetic user message.\n- Keep outbound OpenAI calls proactive: the bridge still calls `triggerGreeting()` on ready when an initial message exists.\n- Preserve configured session instructions for explicit/manual speech and carry the latest response intent through deferred, cancel, and active-response retry paths.\n- Keep session instructions as the base voice instructions; initial greeting instructions are scoped to the first proactive response.\n- Narrow the realtime test callback before invoking optional `sendUserMessage`, fixing the CI `check-test-types` failure on the prior head.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=true pnpm check:test-types` -> passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 74 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check refs/remotes/upstream-safe/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nSigned head: `86d33e4f3b53c564de5e25b609289938245a7a67`.\n\nNote: no live Twilio/OpenAI outbound call was run in this environment.",
